---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Felipe Franco Surface Project" />
<main>
    <div class="sm:h-screen w-screen">
        <Header />
        <div class="sm:pr-[25%] text-center sm:text-right">
            <h1>No place for a surface</h1>
            <p>2022</p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="mt-6 p-4 sm:p-10 sm:w-[95%] w-screen xl:max-w-[60%] sm:max-w-[1000px] mx-auto"
        >
            <div style="padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;">
                <iframe
                    src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/775558567?h=e12545b63a"
                    style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%"
                    allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div><script src="https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js"></script>
        </div>
        <div class="w-screen hidden sm:flex justify-center animate-bounce">
            <a href="#next">
                <img
                    class="w-[30px] cursor-pointer"
                    src="data:image/png;base64,"
                />
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="sm:w-screen w-[90%] max-w-[1000px] mx-auto pb-20" id="next">
        <div
            class="sm:grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-10 text-[12px] text-wrap place-items-center"
        >
            <img class="" src="../Superficie/18.webp" alt="imagen" />
            <div>
                <p class="mt-4 sm:mt-0">
                    Noise is a vertiginous vibration that does not allow to give
                    shape to the things that appear in between. When life
                    becomes saturated, it leaves invisible dirt no choice but to
                    make its home in the cracks, in the crevices, in the
                    margins, where its presence is least heavy. However, when
                    the bristles arrive to scrutinize and eliminate, the
                    particles - the tiny things of life that are capable of
                    sustaining themselves in the void, or even being breathed -
                    seek escape by any means, trying not to stay long outside
                    the ditches that provide them with a habitat. The millenary
                    craft of cleaning, that apparently palliative task related
                    to hygiene and good living, has cleanliness as its fruit and
                    flower, but it has an undeniable root: before impeccability,
                    sin was present; dirt. Sweeping implies moving everything,
                    disturbing the settled and turning dirt into a companion in
                    the tireless dance of two different nomads. On the one hand,
                    the nomad who cleans looking for a more peaceful habitation;
                    on the other hand, the one who inhabits the whole world, who
                    travels and sleeps among the tiles, the cobblestones, the
                    asphalt, the grates and the city lungs. What hides in the
                    mist of the houses, in the shadows of the spaces inhabited
                    by feet and shoes, by crawling paws and hands, what lies
                    like an unnoticed white noise, is what gives shape and
                    meaning to the everyday life of those who live there: it
                    keeps them in vital tension, permanently challenged by the
                    impossibility of the dirt disappearing. If the invisible
                    noise is always there, to whom does a house and its molds
                    belong? To the one who considers himself an inhabitant, or
                    to the inevitable and eternal dirt, which lives in permanent
                    exile and accepts it because it knows how to return to the
                    cracks?
                </p>
                <p class="font-bold pt-8">- Santiago Saldarriaga Montoya</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <img
            class="w-screen"
            loading="lazy"
            src="../Superficie/img1.webp"
            alt=""
        />

        <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gallery" id="gallery"></div>

        <p
            class="sm:w-screen py-20 text-[12px] text-pretty sm:max-w-[800px] mx-auto w-[90%]"
        >
            From an exercise of recognition of the urban space, the project
            raises the possibility of understanding the architectural body
            within the city as an everyday vestige. Buildings of any nature
            that, within the contemporary inhabiting of the city, end up being
            traces of the transformation of a city. As a fundamental part,
            practices and actions for and with architecture are highlighted,
            seeking the way to collect different elements, sonorous, material
            and visual, that compose the idea of an urban identity in the
            context of a city like Medellin. In this way, Sin lugar para una
            superficie is a proposal that, within the formal, proposes an
            installation space that alludes to different surface designs in the
            buildings of the city, but that tend to disappear over time due to
            sound and movement.
        </p>

        <img loading="lazy" src="../Superficie/img2.webp" alt="imagen2" />
    </section>

    <Footer />

    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
            crearGaleria();
        });

        function crearGaleria() {
            let cantidadImg = 16;
            const galer = document.querySelector(".gallery");
            for (let i = 1; i <= cantidadImg; i++) {
                const imagen = document.createElement(
                    "IMG",
                ) as HTMLImageElement;
                imagen.src = `../Superficie/${i}.webp`;
                imagen.alt = `imagen${i}`;
                imagen.width = 500;
                imagen.height = 500;
                imagen.loading = "lazy";
                imagen.classList.add("photos");
                galer.appendChild(imagen);

                imagen.onclick = function () {
                    mostrarImagen(i);
                };
            }
        }

        function mostrarImagen(i) {
            const imagen = document.createElement("IMG") as HTMLImageElement;
            imagen.src = `../Superficie/${i}.webp`;
            imagen.alt = `imagen${i}`;

            const modal = document.createElement("DIV");
            modal.classList.add("modal");
            modal.appendChild(imagen);
            modal.onclick = function (e) {
                if (e.target === modal) {
                    cerrarModal();
                }
            };

            const cerrarModalBtn = document.createElement("BUTTON");
            cerrarModalBtn.textContent = "X";
            cerrarModalBtn.classList.add("btn-cerrar");
            cerrarModalBtn.onclick = cerrarModal;

            const body = document.querySelector("body");
            body.classList.add("overflow-hidden");
            body.appendChild(modal);
            body.appendChild(cerrarModalBtn);
        }

        function cerrarModal() {
            const modal = document.querySelector(".modal");
            const cerrarModalBtn = document.querySelector(".btn-cerrar");
            const body = document.querySelector("body");

            if (modal && cerrarModalBtn) {
                body.removeChild(modal);
                body.removeChild(cerrarModalBtn);
                body.classList.remove("overflow-hidden");
            }
        }
    </script>
</main>
